description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced senior radiographer with significant management experience to provide professional leadership across the cross-sectional imaging department, including CT, MRI and Neuro-Interventional radiology at University Hospital Southampton NHS Foundation Trust (UHS). You will be HCPC registered with an extensive portfolio evidencing both clinical and managerial experience. You will require strong leadership and interpersonal skills with the ability to communicate with staff at all levels within and external to the service, providing advice and guidance where required. You should have strong budgetary management skills and be able to identify cost effective ways of delivery an efficient, high quality and proactive service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are a total of 70 WTE Radiographers and 30 WTE radiology department assistants in the sub-specialty CSI team. The radiology care group incorporates radiographers, scientists, nurses, consultants and trainee radiologists. All areas are supported by HCAs/RDAs with designated administration staff. There are a total of 433.94 WTE staff in the care group with 57 radiology consultants, 40 trainee radiology posts and 179 WTE radiographers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The radiology service provides an out of hours emergency service via an on call/shift rota for all modalities except nuclear medicine. Each modality has a lead superintendent radiographer supported by superintendent radiographers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The care group has a clinical lead who is supported by sub speciality clinical leads. Radiology is well supported by a radiology information team, PACS team, governance facilitator and an operational manager. The care group has strong links with other care groups across the trust and in particular medical physics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We host the Wessex radiology training scheme, which is recognised nationally for its excellent training scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The managed equipment service provides a programme for all new and replacement equipment across the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To manage the staff and equipment required to undertake diagnostic and interventional imaging to meet service needs and clinical demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The operational delivery of the imaging service including the following sub departments: CT, MRI and Neuro- Interventional radiology,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical and managerial governance of the imaging service within the sub departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the operational planning, scheduling and delivery of the service ensuring that the service is safe and sustainable and that staff are supported across the sub departments. You will play a proactive role in the recruitment and retention of staff, ensuring that staff have regular appraisals with the opportunity for personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for managing pay and non-pay budgets matching resources to need and managing workload pressures while at the same time delivering a high quality cost effective service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have recent experience of working within these areas with evidence of professional line management at a senior level, management of organisational change within a rapidly changing environment and the ability to provide leadership and support to staff at all levels. Applicants should have excellent negotiation and communication skills with the ability to modify leadership styles as required. Applicants may be required to deputise for the head of radiography and radiology CGM attending divisional and trust wide meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute teaching Trust’s in England, we can offer learning and development opportunities to help you achieve the career you aspire to. We believe you deserve the best possible surroundings in which to do your job and we want to support you in doing your job to the best of your ability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Trust, we support flexible working and will consider requests taking into account the needs of the service. You’ll have an opportunity to discuss this at interview. Our LiveWell and inspire programme offers opportunities, support and advice, including smoking cessation services, exercise and activity classes, and support for mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS employees are able to access a huge range of NHS discounts, are entitled to a minimum of 35 days paid holiday (pro rata) on appointment, can access on-site nursery facilities (subject to availability), and we offer a generous pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT OUR TRUST AND SOUTHAMPTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS is rated ‘Good’ by the CQC and in the latest national NHS Staff Survey, we were in the top 10 acute trusts for staff engagement and for staff recommending the hospital as a place to work or receive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southampton is an attractive place to live and work situated on the south coast, with an international airport and only an hour on the train from central London. The New Forest National Park and the beaches of the Jurassic coast are also right on our doorstep. The city offers living costs 20% lower than those in London, 13 schools rated outstanding by Ofsted and 13 nearby green spaces to enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADDITIONAL INFORMATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 3rd December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Reid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of radiography&lt;/p&gt;
